00:07:20.930 --> 00:07:28.020
bit so the winds have to push the water up
stream, uphill. It goes until it can't go

00:07:28.020 --> 00:07:36.820
any further so you'll get a deep water in
the Western pacific that's warm and then

00:07:36.820 --> 00:07:41.930
this circulation pattern pushes up cold
water in the East. That's the cooling

00:07:41.930 --> 00:07:47.870
phase of the La Niña. The El Niño is a
little bit different. The Trade Winds can

00:07:47.870 --> 00:07:53.260
suddenly stop for some reason and all this
water rushes downhill. The warm water gets

00:07:53.260 --> 00:08:00.940
heated the second time as it crosses the
pacific slosh up against the North

00:08:00.940 --> 00:08:07.710
American and South American continents.
