00:11:11.940 --> 00:11:16.400
around the Earth's ocean. That tells you
right away that we're doing with a

00:11:16.400 --> 00:11:21.280
comprehensive change in ocean state and
you would expect then that there would be

00:11:21.280 --> 00:11:25.830
other changes in the climate that occurred
at the same time. Other parts of this

00:11:25.830 --> 00:11:32.540
restructuring. As you've probably have
understood from the pictures of polar

00:11:32.540 --> 00:11:39.090
bears, there actually is an Arctic regime
shift in progress. This is first revealed

00:11:39.090 --> 00:11:45.860
by two formal assessments. One in 2005
that used primarily data from before the

00:11:45.860 --> 00:11:51.990
hiatus began and another one only seven
years later. They discovered a major

00:11:51.990 --> 00:11:57.890
change in the distribution of Arctic
heating. During the hiatus has been

00:11:57.890 --> 00:12:03.080
fastest in Spring and Autumn and before it
was fastest in Winter which was consistent

00:12:03.080 --> 00:12:07.190
with the earlier greenhouse warming
models. It's now faster over the oceans

00:12:07.190 --> 00:12:16.070
and the land. These change in patterns
suggested to you that the Arctic developed

00:12:16.070 --> 00:12:23.940
a new warming source that was not as
strong in the previous period. Satellite

00:12:23.940 --> 00:12:30.540
data first began to be collected with
great accuracy later on sea ice area in

00:12:30.540 --> 00:12:39.530
79. Here is the curve that you can see of
the minimum sea ice extent which occurs at

00:12:39.530 --> 00:12:45.020
the end of the warm season in September.
As a function of time, September after

00:12:45.020 --> 00:12:53.980
September since 1979. What you can infer
from this plot is a break in behavior in

00:12:53.980 --> 00:12:59.170
which the sea ice was slowly declining but
oscillating about a slowly declining mean.

00:12:59.170 --> 00:13:04.350
Suddenly there looks like a change in
state. Over this period of time, the sea

00:13:04.350 --> 00:13:12.190
ice area has declined by about 40 percent
and the sea ice volume is down to 25

00:13:12.190 --> 00:13:20.590
percent what it had been in 1979. Here is
the same data that was there in case the

00:13:20.590 --> 00:13:29.320
movie didn't work. This shows you where
the timing of the sea ice decline. There's

00:13:29.320 --> 00:13:35.260
one other thing that has happened during
the period of the hiatus which I think

00:13:35.260 --> 00:13:41.390
will be interesting to Jeff and others.
It's a small analogue of the events that

00:13:41.390 --> 00:13:48.330
slowed the meridional overturn in
circulation. During this hiatus and only

00:13:48.330 --> 00:13:56.260
since about the year 2000, a new pattern
of winds developed over the Arctic ocean.

00:13:56.260 --> 00:14:01.270
It's called the Arctic Dipole Anomaly.
This pair of winds going in opposite

00:14:01.270 --> 00:14:08.540
directions drives ice and sea and fresh
water in the Arctic into the North

00:14:08.540 --> 00:14:15.120
Atlantic where it will shut off or it can
impede. The word collides basically with

00:14:15.120 --> 00:14:21.460
the Gulf Stream. At that collision point
the water sinks to depth. We did see that.

00:14:21.460 --> 00:14:29.110
This is a small event of something that
actually happened in the historical record

00:14:29.110 --> 00:14:36.400
8,000 years ago as the ice sheet was
retreating across North America. As it

00:14:36.400 --> 00:14:42.190
retreated it left behind in the area of
Hudson Bay, a huge glacial lake that was

00:14:42.190 --> 00:14:47.230
contained between the melting ice in one
hand and the moraine that had pushed up on

00:14:47.230 --> 00:14:52.530
the front. These glacial moraines are
unstable and there was a huge outflow of

00:14:52.530 --> 00:14:58.470
water that occurred all at once. There was
a 200 year period of cool climate that

00:14:58.470 --> 00:15:04.290
then recovered. The Columbia River was
also formed this way. What the satellites

00:15:04.290 --> 00:15:10.210
have observed is a great injection of
fresh water into this gyre here, Beaufort

00:15:10.210 --> 00:15:17.150
Gyre, that began at approximately the same
time. That water is lighter and when it

00:15:17.150 --> 00:15:23.020
gets to the saltier Atlantic, the saltier
Atlantic will sink. Here is the next and

00:15:23.020 --> 00:15:29.630
most important point. This sea ice retreat
that I just documented is warming the

00:15:29.630 --> 00:15:36.140
Arctic by a very simple mechanism. When
you replace white ice with blue ocean you

00:15:36.140 --> 00:15:43.950
absorb much more solar energy. The sea ice
itself may reflect half back to space and

00:15:43.950 --> 00:15:50.490
the ocean absorbs 93 percent of the energy
that's falling on it. As the sea ice

00:15:50.490 --> 00:15:58.460
retreats it warms the Arctic. A recent
paper that came out from Scripps measured

00:15:58.460 --> 00:16:06.830
the degree of warming since the satellite
era started in 79. They found that the net

00:16:06.830 --> 00:16:12.750
sea ice retreat adds about six watts per
meter squared but two thirds of the

00:16:12.750 --> 00:16:18.690
heating that took place in that period
occurred in the 10 years between 01 and

00:16:18.690 --> 00:16:25.780
11. Arctic is small but if you average
this over the globe you get 0.21 watts per

00:16:25.780 --> 00:16:31.520
meter squared. Which is about a quarter of
the increase that you would have expected

00:16:31.520 --> 00:16:36.770
from the increase in greenhouse gas at
that time. You have added a new warming

00:16:36.770 --> 00:16:45.620
mechanism that the climate at least in
recent times was not used to. This is a

00:16:45.620 --> 00:16:51.390
picture of the geography of heat transport
in the climate. I put it on even though

00:16:51.390 --> 00:16:57.770
it's complicated. Just to remind you that
the basic circulation of the atmosphere as

00:16:57.770 --> 00:17:02.780
understood from the time of Edmond Halley
was it was heavy and strong warming of the

00:17:02.780 --> 00:17:10.460
ocean and land over the tropics. This heat
was then transported to the North. It was

00:17:10.460 --> 00:17:16.110
a North-South circulation. A North pole,
North equator to pole circulation that's

00:17:16.110 --> 00:17:22.200
the fundamental feature of our climate
transport. If you suddenly add a new

00:17:22.200 --> 00:17:28.000
energy, new heating source at the poles,
particularly the Arctic. Won't you change

00:17:28.000 --> 00:17:34.980
the circulation of heat in the atmosphere
and will this not in fact lead to states

00:17:34.980 --> 00:17:45.240
like the El Niño? What we do know and this
is a question still under active

00:17:45.240 --> 00:17:52.050
investigation. What we do know is that we
have created a 17 or 18 year persistent La

00:17:52.050 --> 00:17:57.950
Niña-like state in the Pacific Ocean and
also similar outflow on the North

00:17:57.950 --> 00:18:04.870
Atlantic, that is lasting longer than most
typical La Niñas. Lasted the whole period

00:18:04.870 --> 00:18:10.550
of time. What this have had an effect on
the climate down below. Because when

00:18:10.550 --> 00:18:18.310
you're in a La Niña state, you bend the
jet stream as you see. You've seen many

00:18:18.310 --> 00:18:23.050
many pictures recently. Anytime you look
at the weather you'll see the jet stream

00:18:23.050 --> 00:18:31.750
dipping deep into Central United States.
We've remained in the state of La Niña

00:18:31.750 --> 00:18:39.110
like jet stream. The weather patterns then
correlate with this. The question is

00:18:39.110 --> 00:18:46.690
global temperature has been constant. You
would expect then that there would be very

00:18:46.690 --> 00:18:53.130
many fewer heat waves right? Or at least
the same number as before. This is not

00:18:53.130 --> 00:19:00.410
proven the case. Here's a remarkable data
analysis generated in Spain where they

00:19:00.410 --> 00:19:07.280
were able to compile the mean Summer
temperature in Europe for the last 500

00:19:07.280 --> 00:19:14.250
years since 1500. What you see is, 5 of
the 10 years in the 2010 were the hottest

00:19:14.250 --> 00:19:21.090
years in the 2010 decade with the hottest
years on record. You also hear about this

00:19:21.090 --> 00:19:27.150
unstable... You hear this bending La Niña
like jet stream. You hear about it in

00:19:27.150 --> 00:19:34.850
other context because in the winter it
brings Arctic air to the South and is then

00:19:34.850 --> 00:19:41.580
responsible for the large snow storms that
we've seen in the past. We also know that

00:19:41.580 --> 00:19:47.770
the La Niña state implies a very dry
climate in California. Something that we

00:19:47.770 --> 00:19:54.490
are presently observing. Here were the
questions. I phrased the hypothesis as a

00:19:54.490 --> 00:20:00.000
set of questions. Did the Arctic warming
associated with the super-El Niño which

00:20:00.000 --> 00:20:05.000
pushed the ice over the edge? Did it
trigger a continuing ice retreat when

00:20:05.000 --> 00:20:10.790
Winter re-growth could not make up for the
previous year's loss? Did Arctic warming,

00:20:10.790 --> 00:20:16.680
by altering the North-South heat flow...
Did it strengthen the Trade Winds, create

00:20:16.680 --> 00:20:22.600
the La Niña bias and enable the persistent
ocean heat sequestration that we've been

00:20:22.600 --> 00:20:28.720
seeing? Did it warming, by altering the
heat flow caused the observed pattern and

00:20:28.720 --> 00:20:34.010
enhancement of extreme event occurrence?
Then finally, how long can this kind of

00:20:34.010 --> 00:20:40.580
thing go on? Will the present dynamical,
quasi-equilibrium be maintained until the

00:20:40.580 --> 00:20:47.471
energy added to the climate system from
ice and snow retreat stops? Thank you.

